The intent of this rule is to ensure that the

attribute can be used to suport personalization. Many users may find it easier to fill out forms if those can be styled or layed out in a way that is familiar to them. Assistive technologies can do this when a form control is marked up in such a way that its purpose can be understood. For instance, assistive technologies could add familiar icons and colors to different fields, making it easier for the user to understand what the form does.
